Iranian Lawmakers Approve Draft Budget Based on $80 Oil Price

-- B y   L a d a n e   N a s s e r i
-- 
2011-04-26T13:26:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-26/iranian-lawmakers-approve-draft-budget-based-on-80-oil-price.html
Iran ’s parliament approved a draft
budget for the Iranian calendar year that started on March 21,
based on a projected oil price of $80 a barrel, the official
 Islamic Republic News Agency  reported.  Lawmakers approved the plan by 90 votes to 61 with nine
abstentions, IRNA said. It didn’t give further details of the
budget’s contents.  Ahmadinejad on Feb. 20 presented a 1,770 trillion-rial
($172 billion) spending plan that he said is intended to reduce
unemployment, build more homes and improve rural  living
conditions . A separate budget of 3,620 trillion rials was
presented for state-owned companies.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ladane Nasseri in Beirut at 
 lnasseri@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net . 